{"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}],"symbolKind":"property","title":"centerOffset","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNAnnotationView(py)centerOffset","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}],"remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNAnnotationView.h#L159","fileName":"MLNAnnotationView.h"}},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"]]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CGVector","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGVector"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, the center point of an annotation view is placed at the geographic"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"coordinate point of the associated annotation. If you do not want the view to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be centered, you can use this property to reposition the view. The offset’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"dy","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" values are measured in points. Positive offset values move the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"annotation view down and to the right, while negative values move it up and to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the left.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set the offset if the annotation view’s visual center point is somewhere other"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"than the logical center of the view. For example, the view may contain an image","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that depicts a downward-pointing pushpin or thumbtack, with the tip positioned"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at the center-bottom of the view. In that case, you would set the offset’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to zero and its ","type":"text"},{"code":"dy","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to half the height of the view.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","title":"MLNAnnotationView","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotationView"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"object that corresponds to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol. When an annotation’s","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"offscreen.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","type":"topic","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"title":"MLNAnnotation","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"objects to handle the display.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotation"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/centerOffset":{"abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","type":"topic","title":"centerOffset","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}],"role":"collection","type":"topic","title":"MapLibre"}}}